9/7/00
  Overnight test result:
    died in 590 mins., due to bad pidbuf link 0xf8 inside dropPic()
    Problem: in BG start up, first I picture is dropped due to seeking DTS.
      But the next B picture is queue.  Finally when dropAnchorUnit is called,
      the first picture, B, has anchorUnitSz==0 and the routine keeps on
      dropping pictures.  Error occurs when the stat queue is empty.
    Solution: start up a channel only when the following three conditions
      are all satisfied:
      - PCR accquired (seekPcr==FALSE)
      - Sequence header found (seekSeqHdr==FALSE)
      - DTS accquired (seekDts==FALSE)

  Error condition during cable pulling:
    - missing reference frame: continue to queue up picture,
          as it will be handled in passAnchorUnit() or dropAnchorUnit()
    - another I/P picture before the closing B: treat it as anchor complete
    - any picture with PicNo >= RefPicNo: if I/P picture, same as case 2,
          otherwise, same as case 1.

    In severe error condition, we need two other checks for
      - picStat queue too long,
      - tp queue too long

    To check for missing reference frame, we set prevRefPicStat to NULL after
      the closing B picture is processed.  Then prevRefPicStat is set to the
      next I/P picture when it is processed.  A B picture with
      prevRefPicStat==NULL indicates missing reference frame.
  
    If an I/P picture is encountered while prevRefPicStat!=NULL, then 
      compute anchorUnitSz, set prevRefPicStat to the new I/P picture,
      and pass or drop that anchor unit.

    The new error handling seems to be quite reliable.  However, when
    bypass, sometime a channel may continue to be in underflow mode
    (jerky motion) after resume.  This problem is not noticable, as
    a splice may clean up the situation.

  BUG: Jin Chern reported a problem at dpi_integ top of tree.  Problem has same
       symptom as forget to define code segment for external routines.  It is
       much often when rate conversion is on.

  BUG: The code sometimes will trap into a mode which keeps on reporting
       PTS, DTS problem, and closing B picture and reference missing problems.


