9/14/00
  - Try to reorganize the procInPicInfo() for channel startup processing.
    Noted that PCR and DTS must be acquried first, sequence header can be
    acquired later.  All three must be acquried before we pass the first
    picture.  However, once the first two are acquired, we can (and must)
    do timebase mapping and prevDet updating.
    However, to simplify code, we only start channel when all three are
    acquired.  Otherwise seekDts and seekSeq will be reset to TRUE.
    
  - Harmonic source occasionally has a frame with bad DTS.
    Need to find out why.  But currenlty we use a more intelligent
    method to decide which DTS to use, the mapped one, or the
    regenerated one, based on their distance to PCR.


