9/26/00
  BUG: Bad PidBuf pointer in copyTp() found once!

  Over rate reduction problem: seems the targetPicSize from statmux is too low.

  PCR jitter problem:
    - Turn off drift correction in statmux and it goes away.
      But need to run long term test to verify whether there is drift.
    - Same jitter problem found in both DiviCom and Harmonic.
    - Same for DPI1_5
    - Trying to go back to 2.1.2DP: Same PCR jitter is observed.  So I guess
      PCR adjustment in dpi only solve long term drift problem, but creates
      severe PCR jitter!
    Solution: turn off drift correction in statmux.  Run time test to verify
      whether buffer problem due to drift is gone!

